        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 9:29PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 928 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Lake Isabella, or 15 miles west of Mount Pleasant,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant...      Shepherd...            Lake Isabella...
Remus...               Millbrook...           Winn...
Blanchard...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Conditions are favorable for the development of weak, brief funnel
clouds. If a funnel cloud is spotted move indoors and report your
sighting to the National Weather Service.</instruction>
